title: UTRGV News: Ibarra earns win on first day of ITA regional
text:
UTRGV News: Ibarra earns win on first day of ITA regional   
COLLEGE STATION — Freshman Dominique Ibarra led the University   tennis team with a singles victory on the first day of the Intercollegiate Tennis Association Texas Regional on Thursday at the George P. Mitchell Tennis Center. 
Ibarra defeated Sam Houston State’s Carrie Casey 6-3, 6-4 in the opening round of 128. Ibarra then lost 6-4, 6-2 to Texas Christian University’s Alexandra Zenovka in the round of 64. 
Senior Reegan Greenwood lost 6-4, 7-5 to Rice’s Fernanda Astete in her opening match, and sophomores Dominique Esparza and Natacha Minc also dropped matched in the round of 128. Greenwood, Esparza and Minc will all be in action Friday in the consolation round. 
In doubles, Greenwood and Minc lost 6-4 to Texas State’s duo of Pippa Carr and Joy Ming Ming Chia in the first round. Esparza and Ibarra had a first-round bye but lost 6-0 to Rice’s team of Solo Zinko and Emily Smith in the round of 32. 
The Vaqueros returns to action with matches starting at 8 a.m. Friday. 
— UTRGV Services
